{
  "_comment": [
    "Pinned, measured artifact list. This file is part of the NixOS image, so its bytes are",
    "covered by the TDX measurement -- changing anything here changes the image hash, which is",
    "exactly the point. Boot fetches each entry, verifies its sha256, and REFUSES TO START on any",
    "mismatch, so it does not matter who serves the bytes: a hostile mirror can only deny service,",
    "never substitute weights or code.",
    "",
    "PINNED: nvidia/Kimi-K2.7-Code-NVFP4 at an immutable commit (67 shards + configs by sha256) and vLLM by OCI digest. Re-pin ONLY via  nix run .#pin-artifacts -- <hf-repo> <revision> [vllm-tag]  -- never hand-write a hash. If files is emptied or a digest cleared, the image fails closed."
  ],
  "vllm": {
    "_comment": "Official vLLM OCI image, pinned by digest (a sha256 over the manifest, covering every layer; podman verifies on pull). TP=8 uses the full HGX B200 board: ~74GB of weights per GPU leaves ~105GB/GPU for KV cache, which is what 400 concurrent users actually need. NOTE --trust-remote-code: vLLM EXECUTES the repo's .py files, so they are pinned by sha256 below and sit inside the measurement -- an auditor can review exactly what code runs.",
    "image": "docker.io/vllm/vllm-openai",
    "digest": "sha256:28568563c4600d2c30b56ceba0ac6b4167c3b0b1d60c4c978d8c769877baa778",
    "args": [
      "--host",
